{{Infobox stadium | name = Al Ahly SC Stadium | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Cairo]], [[Egypt]] | broke_ground = | built = 2018- | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = [[Grass]] | scoreboard = | construction_cost = | suites = | architect = [[Populous (company)]] | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | coordinates = | capacity = 60,000 | record_attendance = | executive_suites = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = [[Al Ahly SC]] }}
'''Al Ahly SC Stadium''' ({{lang-ar|استاد النادي الاهلي}}) is a [[association football|football]] stadium currently under construction in [[Cairo]], [[Egypt]]. It will also host [[Al Ahly SC]] matches, replacing [[Cairo International Stadium]].It will have a capacity of 60,000 spectators.
==Announcement== The president of Al Ahly [[Mahmoud El Khatib]] has revealed on 30 December 2017 that the team has received the support of investors for its new stadium construction project.
The club have announced that the stadium will have 60,000 seats, which will make it the third largest stadium in Egypt after [[Borg El Arab Stadium|Borg El-Arab]] with an 86,000 capacity and the 74,100-seat Cairo International Stadium.
==Architect== Design firm Populous will take the lead on Al Ahly’s project, which is the same architecture company that designed Arsenal’s [[Emirates Stadium]] and London’s [[Wembley Stadium]].
==External links== *[http://www.thestadiumbusiness.com/2018/01/02/al-ahly-president-unveils-stadium-plans/]
