{{infobox sports award | name = Best College Football Player ESPY Award | current_awards = | image = | imagesize = | caption = | description = | presenter = | country = [[United States]] | location = | year = 1993 | year2 = 2001 | website = }} The '''Best College Football Player [[ESPY Award]]''' was presented annually between [[1993 in sports|1993]] and [[2001 in sports|2001]] to the [[college football|collegiate]] [[American football]] player adjudged to be the best in the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|United States]] in a given [[calendar year]]. The award was subsumed in [[2002 in sports|2002]] by the [[Best Male College Athlete ESPY Award]].
The award voting panel comprised variously [[fan (aficionado)|fans]]; [[sports journalism|sportswriter]]s and [[Sports presenter|broadcasters]], sports [[corporate officer|executives]], and retired [[sportsperson]]s, termed collectively ''experts''; and [[List of ESPN personalities|ESPN personalities]] from amongst choices selected by the ESPN Select Nominating Committee. Inasmuch as the [[ESPY Awards#Ceremonies|ESPY Awards ceremonies]] were conducted in February during the pendency of the award's existence, an award presented in a given year is for performance and achievements in the one year theretofore.
