The '''Federação de Futebol do Estado do Espírito Santo''' ([[English language|English]]: Football Association of Espírito Santo state) was founded on May 2, 1917, and it manages all the official [[association football|football]] tournaments within the state of [[Espírito Santo]], which are the [[Campeonato Capixaba]], the [[Campeonato Capixaba (lower levels)|Campeonato Capixaba lower levels]], and the [[Campeonato_Capixaba#Copa_Esp.C3.ADrito_Santo|Copa Espírito Santo]], and represents the clubs at the [[Brazilian Football Confederation|Brazilian Football Confederation (CBF)]].

