{{Infobox stadium | name = Greenwood Baseball Field | nickname = | image = | fullname = | former_names = | location = Campus Drive, [[Asheville, North Carolina]], [[United States|USA]] | coordinates = {{coord|35.617253|-82.570561|display=title,inline}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = Spring 1988 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[University of North Carolina at Asheville]] | operator = University of North Carolina at Asheville | surface = Natural grass | scoreboard = Electronic | estimated_cost = | suites = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 300 | record_attendance = | executive_suites = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = [[UNC Asheville Bulldogs baseball]] ([[Big South Conference|Big South]]) (1988-present) }}
'''Greenwood Baseball Field''' is a [[baseball]] venue in [[Asheville, North Carolina]], [[United States]]. It is home to the [[UNC Asheville Bulldogs baseball]] team of the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]] [[Division I (NCAA)|Division I]] [[Big South Conference]]. The facility opened in 1988.<ref name=facil>{{cite web|title=Greenwood Baseball Field|url=http://www.uncabulldogs.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=19200&KEY=&ATCLID=1158274|work=UNCA Bulldogs|accessdate=4 February 2012|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/65CfI7Je4?url=http://www.uncabulldogs.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=19200&KEY=&ATCLID=1158274|archivedate=2012-02-04|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> It has a capacity of 300 spectators.<ref name=mg>{{cite web|title=2011 Baseball Media Guide|url=http://www.uncabulldogs.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=19200&ATCLID=1441725|work=UNCA Bulldogs|accessdate=4 February 2012|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/65CfMru3O?url=http://www.uncabulldogs.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=19200&ATCLID=1441725|archivedate=2012-02-04|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> It features an electronic scoreboard, [[Dugout (baseball)|dugout]]s, and a natural grass surface.<ref name=facil />
UNC Asheville also uses [[McCormick Field]], home of the [[Asheville Tourists]] [[minor league baseball]] team, for a portion of its schedule.<ref name=11sched>{{cite web |last=Foley |first=Brian |title=UNC-Asheville Releases 2011 Schedule |url=http://www.collegebaseballdaily.com/2011/01/13/unc-asheville-2011-schedule/ |work=College Baseball Daily |publisher=CBD News Source |accessdate=4 February 2012 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/65Cfbb4pl?url=http://www.collegebaseballdaily.com/2011/01/13/unc-asheville-2011-schedule/ |archivedate=4 February 2012 |date=13 January 2012 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref name=sched>{{cite web|title=Bulldog Baseball Announces 2012 Schedule|url=http://www.uncabulldogs.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=19200&ATCLID=205373053|work=UNCA Bulldogs|accessdate=4 February 2012|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/65CfTG4fY?url=http://www.uncabulldogs.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=19200&ATCLID=205373053|archivedate=2012-02-04|date=2 February 2012|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref>
