{{Infobox organization |name = Uganda Cricket Association |image = |caption = |motto = |headquarters = [[Kampala]], [[Uganda]] |leader_title = Chairman |leader_name = {{flagicon|UGA}} [[Bashir Badu Ansasira]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1446530/uganda-cricket-association-elect-badu-board|title=Uganda Cricket Association elects Badu, new board|access-date = 3 August 2017}}</ref> |leader_title2 = Secretary |leader_name2 = {{flagicon|UGA}} [[Eric Kamara]] |leader_title3 = CEO |leader_name3 = {{flagicon|UGA}} [[Justine Ligyalingi]] |key_people = |website = [http://www.ugandacricket.com/ Uganda Cricket] }} '''Uganda Cricket Association''' is the official [[Sport governing body|governing body]] of the sport of [[cricket]] in [[Uganda]]. Its current headquarters is in [[Kampala]], [[Uganda]]. Uganda Cricket Association is Uganda's representative at the [[International Cricket Council]] and is an associate member and has been a member of that body since 1998. It is also a member of the [[African Cricket Association]].
Justine Ligyalingi is the CEO of UCA(Uganda Cricket Association). Henry Okecho is the Development Manager and Martin Ondeko is the Operations Manager.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ugandacricket.com/index.php/contact|title=Uganda Cricket Association Contacts|access-date = 25 August 2016 }}</ref>
