'''Weynay Ghebresilasie''' (born 24 March 1994 in Gheza Hamle, [[Eritrea]]) is an [[Eritrea]]n runner who specializes in the [[3000 metres steeplechase]].<ref>{{IAAF name|id=262559|name=Weynay Ghebresilasie}}</ref> He competed in [[Athletics at the 2012 Summer Olympics – Men's 3000 metres steeplechase|that event]] at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]], coming tenth in his heat, and was the flag bearer of the [[Eritrea at the 2012 Summer Olympics|Eritrean team]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.london2012.com/athlete/ghebresilasie-weynay-1061666/|title=Olympic Results, Gold Medalists and Official Records|date=2017-02-23|work=International Olympic Committee|access-date=2018-04-09|language=en}}</ref><ref name=london2012ocfb>{{cite news| author = Staff | title=London 2012 Opening Ceremony - Flag Bearers |url=http://www.olympic.org/Documents/Games_London_2012/Flagbearers.pdf |accessdate=10 August 2012| work = [[Olympics]]}}</ref> He also placed sixth at the [[2012 World Junior Championships in Athletics]] that year.
Subsequent to the Olympics, he sought [[political asylum]] in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2012/aug/15/eritrea-runner-seeks-asylum-uk|title=Eritrea's flag-carrying runner seeks asylum in UK to flee repressive regime|last=Quinn|first=Ben|date=2012-08-14|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=2018-04-09}}</ref> He joined [[Sunderland Harriers & Athletic Club]] and stated that if successful in his asylum application he would like to run for Great Britain.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/athletics/21368236 Weynay Ghebresilasie: Running for freedom in Sunderland]. BBC Sport. Retrieved on 2013-04-07.</ref>
